cs.IT, cs.COMM, cs.SY, cs.DS, cs.MM 

Reasoning: 
1. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper discusses information-theoretic results related to low-precision ADC and investigates the achievable performance under quantization. 
2. cs.COMM (Communications and Networking) - The paper focuses on the impact of low-precision ADC on a carrier asynchronous system and considers transmission over the block noncoherent AWGN channel. 
3. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper proposes a specific receiver architecture that quantizes only the phase of the received signal and investigates the structure of the transition density of the resulting phase-quantized block noncoherent channel. 
4. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) - The paper discusses low-complexity procedures for computing the channel capacity and for block demodulation. 
5. cs.MM (Multimedia) - The paper mentions dithering the constellation to improve performance in the face of drastic quantization, which is a technique commonly used in multimedia applications.
